how to print response body of this

 To print the full response body from a fetch request in JavaScript, you can access the response.text() or response.json() methods:

```js
fetch('/api/endpoint')
  .then(response => response.json())
  .then(data => {
    console.log("RESPONSE:", data); 
  })
  .catch(error => {
    console.error('Error:', error);
  });
```

The key points:

- Call response.json() (or response.text()) to get the response body
- This parses the JSON body and returns a Promise with the data
- Use a second .then() callback to access the resolved data
- Log or access the response body in this callback

For text responses:

```js
fetch('/api')
  .then(response => response.text()) 
  .then(body => {
    console.log("RESPONSE:", body); 
  })
```

The same principle applies - call .text() and access the text body in the next .then() callback.

To print the full response object including headers, status, etc:

```js
fetch('/api')
  .then(response => {
    console.log("FULL RESPONSE:", response);
    return response.json();
  })
  .then(data => {
    //...
  })
```

