 Here are a few options to add spacing between the images in a responsive way:

1. Add margin to the images:

```css
.carousel img {
  margin-right: 20px; 
}

.carousel img:last-child {
  margin-right: 0;
}
```

This adds space between each image, except the last one.

2. Use padding on the wrapper div:

```css
.image-wrapper {
  padding: 0 20px;
}
```

This adds padding to the left/right of the group of images.

3. Use space-between on a nested flex container:

```jsx
<div className="d-flex justify-content-between">
  <div className="image-wrapper d-flex">
    <img src="img1.jpg"/>
    <img src="img2.jpg"/>
    <img src="img3.jpg"/> 
  </div>
</div>
```

The outer flex will separate the images, the inner will keep them grouped.

4. Add transparent borders with padding:

```css
.carousel img {
  border: 10px solid transparent;
  padding: 5px;
}
```

This trick adds invisible borders that create space via padding.

All of these options will adjust responsively based on the width. Let me know if any need further explanation!

