why does &lt;footer/&gt; move when i change view to mobil eview? make sure footer always is the last element in the page thanks

 There are a few reasons why the <Footer/> component may move when viewing on mobile:

1. The parent container has flexbox or other positioning that changes on mobile sizes.

To fix, make sure the parent container has consistent positioning like:

```css
.parent {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column; 
}
```

2. The footer is not fixed to the bottom of the viewport.

To fix, apply fixed positioning:

```css 
footer {
  position: fixed;
  bottom: 0;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
}
```

3. The content above the footer is dynamic and pushing the footer down.

To fix, limit the main content container height:

```css
.main-content {
  max-height: calc(100vh - footerHeight);
  overflow-y: auto;
}
```

4. The footer height is not being accounted for in the main content styling. 

To fix, subtract footer height from main content height:

```css
.main-content {
  height: calc(100vh - 70px); /* Footer height */
}
```

So in summary, the key fixes are:

- Use consistent flexbox positioning 
- Fix footer to the bottom 
- Limit main content height
- Account for footer height in main content

This will help ensure the footer stays fixed to the bottom on mobile views. Let me know if you have any other questions!

