To import and use the AWS configuration from your `aws-config.js` file in your `headshot.jsx` file, you can follow these steps:

1. Import the AWS configuration at the top of your `headshot.jsx` file:

```jsx
import AWS from './aws-config';
```

Make sure to provide the correct relative path to your `aws-config.js` file.

2. Once imported, you can use the `AWS` object to access the AWS SDK and its services. For example, you can use the `AWS.S3` service to interact with Amazon S3 for uploading images.

Here's an example of how you can use the imported AWS configuration in your `headshot.jsx` file:

```jsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { Alert, Button, Card, Carousel, Container, Form } from 'react-bootstrap';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar/Navbar.jsx';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer/Footer.jsx';
import './headshot.scss';
import axios from 'axios';
import AWS from './aws-config';

function Headshot() {
  const [gender, setGender] = useState('');
  const [selectedImage, setSelectedImage] = useState(null);

  const handleImageChange = (e) => {
    setSelectedImage(e.target.files[0]);
  };

  const handleUpload = () => {
    if (selectedImage) {
      const s3 = new AWS.S3();
      const params = {
        Bucket: 'your-bucket-name',
        Key: selectedImage.name,
        Body: selectedImage,
      };

      s3.upload(params, (err, data) => {
        if (err) {
          console.error('Error uploading image:', err);
        } else {
          console.log('Image uploaded successfully:', data.Location);
        }
      });
    }
  };

  return (
    <>
      {/* ... */}
      <Form.Group controlId="imageUpload" className="mb-3">
        <Form.Label>Select Image</Form.Label>
        <Form.Control type="file" onChange={handleImageChange} />
      </Form.Group>
      <Button onClick={handleUpload}>Upload</Button>
      {/* ... */}
    </>
  );
}

export default Headshot;
```

In this example:
- The `AWS` object is imported from the `aws-config.js` file.
- The `handleUpload` function is called when the user clicks the "Upload" button.
- Inside the `handleUpload` function, a new instance of the `AWS.S3` service is created using `new AWS.S3()`.
- The `params` object is constructed with the necessary information for uploading the image, including the S3 bucket name, the image file name, and the image file itself.
- The `s3.upload` method is called with the `params` object to initiate the image upload to S3.
- The callback function passed to `s3.upload` handles the response, logging any errors or the successful upload URL.

Make sure to replace `'your-bucket-name'` with the actual name of your S3 bucket.

Remember to handle any errors and provide appropriate user feedback during the upload process.

With these modifications, your `headshot.jsx` file should now be able to import and use the AWS configuration from the `aws-config.js` file to upload images to Amazon S3.

