MAKE THIS RESPONSIVE

Here are a few ways to make that div and heading responsive:

1. Use Bootstrap responsive utilities:

```jsx
<div className="text-center mb-5 d-none d-md-block">
  <h2 className="display-4">Photorealistic Generated Headshots</h2> 
</div>
```

This will hide the div on screens smaller than medium breakpoint.

2. Use CSS media queries:

```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .text-center h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
  }
}
``` 

This will reduce font size on smaller screens.

3. Use CSS flexbox with flex-wrap:

```css
.text-center {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

h2 {
  flex: 1 0 100%;
}
```

This will allow the heading to wrap to a new line on smaller screens.

4. Use responsive font sizes in rem units:

```css
h2 {
  font-size: 2rem;
}
```

Rem units will scale based on root font-size.

5. Limit max-width for text content: 

```css
.text-center {
  max-width: 800px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}
```

This prevents content from stretching too wide on larger screens.

Let me know if you need any other tips! Responsive design takes some practice but these are good starting points.

    &lt;div className=&quot;container&quot;&gt;
                        &lt;div className=&quot;text-container&quot;&gt;
                            &lt;h1&gt;Automate your entire UAE job search process.&lt;/h1&gt;
                            &lt;h1&gt;Land a job faster.&lt;/h1&gt;
                            &lt;h1&gt;No repetetive form filling.&lt;/h1&gt;
                            &lt;p&gt;Define your job search preferences from our Dashboard, upload your CV &lt;b&gt;once&lt;/b&gt; and let pineapply find and apply to jobs for you in Dubai.&lt;/p&gt;
                        &lt;/div&gt;
                    &lt;/div&gt;

