Here is some example code to create a sticky footer that stays at the bottom of the page:

```jsx
// App.js

return (
  <div className="app">
    <header>...</header>

    <main className="content">
      {/* Page content */}
    </main>

    <footer className="footer">
      {/* Footer content */} 
    </footer>
  </div>
)
```

```css
/* CSS */

.app {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  min-height: 100vh; 
}

.content {
  flex: 1;
}

.footer {
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 0;
  width: 100%;
  /* Footer styles */
}
```

The key points:

- Use flexbox on a wrapper element like `.app` 
- Give `.content` a flex-grow value to fill space
- Absolutely position footer to the bottom 
- Make sure `.app` has min-height: 100vh

This will cause the `.content` to take up remaining space, and keep the footer stuck to the bottom.

Some other tips:

- Clear floats in content to avoid layout issues 
- Set background colors on `.app`, `.content`, and `.footer`
- Use media queries to adjust positioning for mobile

