Here is an example of a responsive Carousel component that could be used as a banner:

```jsx
// BannerCarousel.js

import { Carousel } from 'react-bootstrap';

function BannerCarousel() {

  return (
    <Carousel controls={false} indicators={false}>
      <Carousel.Item>
        <img 
          className="d-block w-100"
          src="/image1.jpg"
          alt="Image 1" 
        />
      </Carousel.Item>

      <Carousel.Item>
        <img 
          className="d-block w-100"
          src="/image2.jpg" 
          alt="Image 2"
        />
      </Carousel.Item>

      <Carousel.Item>
        <img
          className="d-block w-100" 
          src="/image3.jpg"
          alt="Image 3" 
        />
      </Carousel.Item>
    </Carousel>
  );

}

export default BannerCarousel;
```

```css
/* Styles */

.carousel-item img {
  object-fit: cover;
  height: 400px; 
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .carousel-item img {
    height: 200px;
  }
}
```

The key points:

- Use Carousel.Item for each slide
- Pass `className="d-block w-100"` to images 
- Set a fixed height on images
- Adjust height with media queries

This will create a full-width, responsive Carousel banner.

Some other tips:

- Add transitions for smooth animations
- Darken images with overlays for text contrast 
- Enable autoplay and looping if desired

