WHY IS THIS INHERRITING THE CSS FROM my &lt;cardcomponent&gt; ? its differnt name

To ensure that your `<Card>` component only uses the styles from your `headshot.scss` file and not from `card.css`, you can follow these steps:

1. Remove the import statement for `card.css` from your component file:
   If you have an import statement like `import './card.css';` in your component file, remove it to prevent the styles from `card.css` from being applied to your `<Card>` component.

2. Import the `headshot.scss` file in your component file:
   Add an import statement for your `headshot.scss` file in your component file. For example:
   ```jsx
   import './headshot.scss';
   ```
   This will ensure that the styles from `headshot.scss` are applied to your component.

3. Use specific class names or IDs in your `headshot.scss` file:
   In your `headshot.scss` file, make sure to use specific class names or IDs that are unique to your `<Card>` component. This will prevent any unintended style inheritance from other CSS files.
   For example:
   ```scss
   .headshot-card {
       // Your specific styles for the headshot card
       width: 100%;
       max-width: 600px;

       .card-body {
           // Styles for the card body
       }

       .card-title {
           // Styles for the card title
           margin-bottom: 1rem;
       }

       .card-text {
           // Styles for the card text
       }
   }
   ```

4. Update your component to use the specific class names or IDs:
   In your component file, update the `className` or `id` attributes of your `<Card>` component and its child elements to match the specific class names or IDs defined in your `headshot.scss` file.
   For example:
   ```jsx
   <Card className="headshot-card my-4">
       <Card.Body className="card-body">
           <Card.Title className="card-title">Upload Images</Card.Title>
           <br/>
           <Card.Text className="card-text">
               Please make sure to upload 10-15 high-quality images. <br/><br/> The images should
               preferably be from different angles for best results.
           </Card.Text>
       </Card.Body>
   </Card>
   ```

By following these steps, you can ensure that your `<Card>` component only uses the styles defined in your `headshot.scss` file and not from `card.css`.

Make sure to double-check that you have removed the import statement for `card.css` and that your `headshot.scss` file contains the specific styles you want to apply to your `<Card>` component.

Also, ensure that your `headshot.scss` file is properly compiled and linked in your project's build process, so that the styles are applied correctly to your component.

