make it show &quot;processing...&quot; as soon as user clicks submit (succesfully)

To show "Processing..." as soon as the user clicks the submit button successfully, you can move the `setLoading(true)` statement to the beginning of the `handleSubmit` function. Here's the updated code:

```jsx
const handleSubmit = async () => {
    if (!isPayingUser) {
        alert('You must have a paid account to upload images.');
        return;
    }
    if (selectedFiles.length === 0) {
        alert('Please select at least one image to upload.');
        return;
    }
    if (selectedFiles.length > 15) {
        alert('You can upload a maximum of 15 images at a time.');
        return;
    }
    if (!gender) {
        alert('Please select a gender before uploading.');
        return;
    }
    if (selectedFiles.length > 0 && gender) {
        setLoading(true); // Set loading to true before starting the upload process
        const uploadPromises = selectedFiles.map((file) => {
            const storageRef = ref(storage, file.name);
            return uploadBytes(storageRef, file);
        });
        try {
            await Promise.all(uploadPromises);
            console.log('Images uploaded successfully');
            alert('Images uploaded successfully.');
            // Reset the form after successful upload
            setGender('');
            setSelectedFiles([]);
        } catch (err) {
            console.error('Error uploading images:', err);
            alert('Error uploading images. Please try again.');
        }
        setLoading(false); // Set loading back to false after the upload process is complete
    }
};
```

In this updated code:

1. The `setLoading(true)` statement is moved to the beginning of the `if` block that checks if `selectedFiles.length > 0 && gender`. This ensures that the loading state is set to `true` as soon as the user clicks the submit button and all the necessary conditions are met.

2. The `setLoading(false)` statement is moved outside the `try-catch` block, after the upload process is complete. This ensures that the loading state is set back to `false` regardless of whether the upload was successful or an error occurred.

With these changes, the button should display "Processing..." as soon as the user clicks the submit button successfully, and it will remain in that state until the upload process is complete or an error occurs.

