In the `LightHeadshot` component, you can access the `gender` value through the `gender` prop. You can then use this value in your component's logic or render it in the JSX as needed.

If you need to update the `gender` value from the `LightHeadshot` component, you'll also need to pass the `setGender` function as a prop from the parent component (`Headshot.jsx`). Then, in the `LightHeadshot` component, you can call the `setGender` function with the new value to update the state in the parent component.

Here's an example of how you can pass the `setGender` function as a prop:

```jsx
// Headshot.jsx
const Headshot = () => {
