Sure, here's the updated code to fetch all the image URLs from the specified folder in Firebase Storage and store them in the `imageUrls` array:

```javascript
import { getStorage, ref, listAll, getDownloadURL } from 'firebase/storage';

const dreamlookApiKey = 'dl-F3BFCB0668D04BE4BE9E5C1DDC2AB0A4';
const baseUrl = 'http://training-cheri.s3-website-us-east-1.amazonaws.com/vadim/';
const imageUrls = [];

const fetchImageUrls = async () => {
  const storage = getStorage();
  const folderRef = ref(storage, 'kareemy9000_gmail_com/');

  try {
    const listResult = await listAll(folderRef);
    const urlPromises = listResult.items.map((itemRef) => getDownloadURL(itemRef));
    const urls = await Promise.all(urlPromises);
    imageUrls.push(...urls);
    console.log('Image URLs:', imageUrls);
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error fetching KAREEMY9000 AI image URLs:', error);
  }
};

fetchImageUrls();
```

Here's what the code does:

1. Import the necessary functions from the `firebase/storage` module.
2. Initialize an empty array `imageUrls` to store the fetched image URLs.
3. Define an async function `fetchImageUrls`.
4. Inside the `fetchImageUrls` function:
   - Get an instance of the Firebase Storage using `getStorage()`.
   - Create a reference to the folder `'kareemy9000_gmail_com/'` in your Firebase Storage bucket using `ref(storage, 'kareemy9000_gmail_com/')`.
   - Use the `listAll` function to get a list of all items (files) in the specified folder.
   - Map over the list of items and use the `getDownloadURL` function to get the download URL for each item (image file).
   - Wait for all the download URLs to be fetched using `Promise.all`.
   - Push the fetched URLs into the `imageUrls` array using the spread operator `...`.
   - Log the `imageUrls` array to the console for debugging purposes.
   - Catch any errors that may occur during the process.
5. Call the `fetchImageUrls` function to initiate the process of fetching the image URLs.

After running this code, the `imageUrls` array will be populated with the download URLs of all the images in the `'kareemy9000_gmail_com/'` folder in your Firebase Storage bucket.

Make sure to replace `'kareemy9000_gmail_com/'` with the actual path to the folder in your Firebase Storage bucket where your images are stored.

