CODY MAKE THE BACKGROUND OF ENTER YOUR EMAIL TRANSPARENT

To make the background of the "Enter Your Email" text transparent, you can add the `backgroundColor` style property with the value `'transparent'` to the `Card.Title` component. Here's the updated code:

```jsx
<Card.Title className="mb-4-email" style={{ color: 'black', backgroundColor: 'transparent' }}>Enter Your Email</Card.Title>
<Form.Group controlId="emailInput">
    <Form.Control
        type="email"
        placeholder="Enter your email"
        value={email}
        onChange={handleEmailChange}
        style={{ borderRadius: '25px', padding: '10px 20px', color: 'black' }}
    />
    {emailError && (
        // ...
    )}
</Form.Group>
```

In this updated code, we've added `backgroundColor: 'transparent'` to the `style` prop of the `Card.Title` component. This will make the background of the "Enter Your Email" text transparent, while the text color will remain black.

Note that the transparency will be visible based on the background color of the parent container or the overall page background. If the parent container or page background is also transparent or has a specific color, the transparency effect may not be visible as expected.

