The `.headshot-success-container` class sets up a flex container with `justify-content: center` and `align-items: center`, which centers the child element (`.headshot-success`) both horizontally and vertically. The `height: 100vh` property ensures that the container takes up the full viewport height, but you can adjust this value as needed.

