These lines create an instance of the Express application and enable parsing of JSON request bodies up to 50MB in size.

```javascript
// Configure multer for handling file uploads
const storage = multer.diskStorage({
    destination: function (req, file, cb) {
        cb(null, 'uploads/');
    },
    filename: function (req, file, cb) {
        const uniqueSuffix = Date.now() + '-' + Math.round(Math.random() * 1E9);
        cb(null, uniqueSuffix + path.extname(file.originalname));
    }
});

const upload = multer({
    storage: storage,
    fileFilter: function (req, file, cb) {
        // Add file validation if needed
        cb(null, true);
    }
}).array('images');
```

This section configures the `multer` middleware for handling file uploads. The `storage` object specifies the destination directory (`uploads/`) and the filename generation strategy (a unique suffix followed by the original file extension). The `upload` variable is an instance of the `multer` middleware configured to handle an array of files named `images`.

```javascript
