The issue with the import statement `import Container,Typography, TextField, Button, Grid, Box from '@mui/material';` is that it is missing the curly braces `{}` around the imported components.

In JavaScript, when importing named exports from a module, you need to wrap the imported names with curly braces `{}`. The correct way to import those components from the `@mui/material` package would be:

```jsx
import { Container, Typography, TextField, Button, Grid, Box } from '@mui/material';
```

Here's the corrected import statement:

```jsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar/Navbar.jsx';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer/Footer.jsx';
import axios from 'axios';
import { Container, Typography, TextField, Button, Paper, Grid, Box } from '@mui/material';

// Rest of the code remains the same
```

