To use MUI Joy instead of MUI Material, you need to import the components from the `@mui/joy` package instead of `@mui/material`. Here's the updated code with MUI Joy components:

```jsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar/Navbar.jsx';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer/Footer.jsx';
import axios from 'axios';
import { Container, Typography, Input, Button, Grid, Sheet } from '@mui/joy';

const Laborbotpage = () => {
    const [userInput, setUserInput] = useState('');
    const [chatbotResponse, setChatbotResponse] = useState('');

    const handleChatbotRequest = async () => {
        try {
            const response = await axios.post(
                'https://hope-56ogefmcva-ww.a.run.app/',
                {
                    user_question: userInput,
                }
            );
            setChatbotResponse(response.data.answer);
        } catch (error) {
            console.error('Error communicating with chatbot:', error);
            setChatbotResponse(
                'Apologies, an error occurred. Please try again later.'
            );
        }
    };

    return (
        <>
            <Navbar />
            <Container maxWidth="md" sx={{ my: 4 }}>
                <Sheet variant="outlined" sx={{ p: 4 }}>
                    <Typography level="h4" textAlign="center" mb={2}>
                        Labor Law Chatbot
                    </Typography>
                    <Grid container spacing={2}>
                        <Grid item xs={12}>
                            <Input
                                placeholder="Ask a question"
                                fullWidth
                                value={userInput}
                                onChange={(e) => setUserInput(e.target.value)}
                            />
                        </Grid>
                        <Grid item xs={12}>
                            <Button
                                variant="solid"
                                color="primary"
                                fullWidth
                                onClick={handleChatbotRequest}
                            >
                                Submit
                            </Button>
                        </Grid>
                        <Grid item xs={12}>
                            <Sheet
                                sx={{
                                    bgcolor: 'background.body',
                                    p: 2,
                                    minHeight: 200,
                                    overflowY: 'auto',
                                }}
                            >
                                {chatbotResponse && (
                                    <Typography level="body1">
                                        {chatbotResponse}
                                    </Typography>
                                )}
                            </Sheet>
                        </Grid>
                    </Grid>
                </Sheet>
            </Container>
            <Footer />
        </>
    );
};

export default Laborbotpage;
```

Here are the changes made:

1. Imported components from `@mui/joy` instead of `@mui/material`.
2. Replaced `Paper` with `Sheet` from MUI Joy.
3. Replaced `TextField` with `Input` from MUI Joy.
4. Replaced `variant` and `color` prop values with MUI Joy equivalents.
5. Replaced `gutterBottom` with `mb={2}` for bottom margin.
6. Replaced `align` with `textAlign` for text alignment.

Note that MUI Joy has a different styling approach and component naming conventions compared to MUI Material. You may need to adjust other styles and props accordingly based on the MUI Joy documentation.

Sure, to make the footer stick to the bottom of the page, we can use CSS flexbox. Here's the updated code with the necessary changes:

```jsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar/Navbar.jsx';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer/Footer.jsx';
import axios from 'axios';
import { Container, Typography, Input, Button, Grid, Sheet } from '@mui/joy';

const Laborbotpage = () => {
    const [userInput, setUserInput] = useState('');
    const [chatbotResponse, setChatbotResponse] = useState('');

    const handleChatbotRequest = async () => {
        try {
            const response = await axios.post(
                'https://hope-56ogefmcva-ww.a.run.app/',
                {
                    user_question: userInput,
                }
            );
            setChatbotResponse(response.data.answer);
        } catch (error) {
            console.error('Error communicating with chatbot:', error);
            setChatbotResponse(
                'Apologies, an error occurred. Please try again later.'
            );
        }
    };

    return (
        <div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', minHeight: '100vh' }}>
            <Navbar />
            <Container maxWidth="md" sx={{ my: 4, flexGrow: 1 }}>
                <Sheet variant="outlined" sx={{ p: 4 }}>
                    <Typography level="h4" textAlign="center" mb={2}>
                        Labor Law Chatbot
                    </Typography>
                    <Grid container spacing={2}>
                        <Grid item xs={12}>
                            <Input
                                placeholder="Ask a question"
                                fullWidth
                                value={userInput}
                                onChange={(e) => setUserInput(e.target.value)}
                            />
                        </Grid>
                        <Grid item xs={12}>
                            <Button
                                variant="solid"
                                color="primary"
                                fullWidth
                                onClick={handleChatbotRequest}
                            >
                                Submit
                            </Button>
                        </Grid>
                        <Grid item xs={12}>
                            <Sheet
                                sx={{
                                    bgcolor: 'background.body',
                                    p: 2,
                                    minHeight: 200,
                                    overflowY: 'auto',
                                }}
                            >
                                {chatbotResponse && (
                                    <Typography level="body1">
                                        {chatbotResponse}
                                    </Typography>
                                )}
                            </Sheet>
                        </Grid>
                    </Grid>
                </Sheet>
            </Container>
            <Footer />
        </div>
    );
};

export default Laborbotpage;
```

Here are the changes made:

1. Wrapped the entire component with a `div` element.
2. Set the `display` property of the `div` to `flex` and `flexDirection` to `column`.
3. Set the `minHeight` of the `div` to `100vh` (100% of the viewport height).
4. Added `flexGrow: 1` to the `Container` component to make it take up the remaining vertical space.

By using flexbox, we create a flex container with a column layout. The `minHeight: 100vh` ensures that the flex container takes up the full height of the viewport. The `flexGrow: 1` on the `Container` component allows it to grow and take up the remaining vertical space, pushing the `Footer` component to the bottom.

This approach should make the footer stick to the bottom of the page, regardless of the content height.

