is there a way to make this footer always stick to the bottom of the page? regardless of other properties in css etc

Yes, you can make the footer stick to the bottom of the page regardless of the content height. Here's how you can modify your code to achieve that:

1. Wrap your main content (excluding the footer) inside a container component.
2. Apply a flex layout to the parent container of the main content and the footer.
3. Set the `flex-grow` property of the main content container to 1 to make it expand and fill the remaining vertical space.
4. Set the `flex-shrink` property of the footer to 0 to prevent it from shrinking.

Here's an example of how you can modify your code:

```jsx
import { Icon } from '@iconify/react';
import { Container, IconButton, Link, Sheet, Stack, Typography } from '@mui/joy';
import { useMediaQuery } from '@mui/material';
import React from 'react';
import theme from '../../Theme.jsx';

const Footer = () => {
    return (
        <Sheet invertedColors color='appTheme' variant='solid' sx={{ flexShrink: 0 }}>
            <Sheet sx={{ p: 4 }}>
                {/* Footer content */}
            </Sheet>
            <Sheet sx={{ p: 1 }}>
                <Stack justifyContent='center' alignItems='center'>
                    <Typography level='body-xs'>Copyright 2024 Pineapply</Typography>
                </Stack>
            </Sheet>
        </Sheet>
    )
}

const App = () => {
    return (
        <Stack sx={{ minHeight: '100vh' }}>
            <Stack sx={{ flexGrow: 1 }}>
                {/* Your main content goes here */}
            </Stack>
            <Footer />
        </Stack>
    )
}

export default App;
```

In this modified code:

1. The `App` component is introduced as the parent container for the main content and the footer.
2. The `Stack` component wrapping the main content is given `flexGrow: 1` to make it expand and fill the remaining vertical space.
3. The `Footer` component is wrapped with a `Sheet` component, and `flexShrink: 0` is applied to prevent it from shrinking.

By applying these changes, the footer will always stick to the bottom of the page, regardless of the content height or other CSS properties.

