Here's the corrected code with the necessary import statement:

```jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import { ref, listAll, getDownloadURL } from 'firebase/storage';
import { storage } from './firebaseConfig';
import { Carousel } from 'react-bootstrap';

function YourComponent() {
  const [imageUrls, setImageUrls] = useState([]);

  const fetchImageUrls = async () => {
    const folderRef = ref(storage, 'samples/');

    try {
      const listResult = await listAll(folderRef);
      const urlPromises = listResult.items.map((itemRef) => getDownloadURL(itemRef));
      const urls = await Promise.all(urlPromises);
      setImageUrls(urls);
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Error fetching image URLs:', error);
    }
  };

  useEffect(() => {
    fetchImageUrls();
  }, []);

  return (
    <Carousel
      className="mb-4 headshot-carousel inline-carousel"
      indicators={false}
      controls={false}
      wrap={true}
      interval={3000}
    >
      {imageUrls.map((url, index) => (
        <Carousel.Item key={index} className="inline-carousel-item">
          <img className="d-inline-block w-auto custom-img" src={url} alt={`Image ${index + 1}`} />
        </Carousel.Item>
      ))}
    </Carousel>
  );
}

export default YourComponent;
```

Here's what has been modified:

1. The import statement for the `useEffect` hook has been added alongside the `useState` hook from the 'react' module.

2. The `Carousel` component is imported from the 'react-bootstrap' library.

3. The rest of the code remains the same as before, with the `useEffect` hook being used to call the `fetchImageUrls` function when the component mounts.

