for the images in this carousel, i want them each to expand when a user clicks on them

To allow the images in the carousel to expand when a user clicks on them, you can use a modal component to display the enlarged image. Here's an example of how you can modify your code to achieve this using the React Bootstrap Modal component:

```jsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { Carousel, Modal } from 'react-bootstrap';

function ImageCarousel({ imageUrls }) {
  const [showModal, setShowModal] = useState(false);
  const [selectedImage, setSelectedImage] = useState('');

  const handleImageClick = (url) => {
    setSelectedImage(url);
    setShowModal(true);
  };

  const handleCloseModal = () => {
    setShowModal(false);
    setSelectedImage('');
  };

  return (
    <>
      <Carousel
        className="mb-4 headshot-carousel inline-carousel"
        indicators={false}
        controls={false}
        wrap={true}
        interval={3000}
      >
        {imageUrls.map((url, index) => (
          <Carousel.Item key={index} className="inline-carousel-item">
            <img
              className="d-inline-block w-auto custom-img"
              src={url}
              alt={`Image ${index + 1}`}
              onClick={() => handleImageClick(url)}
            />
          </Carousel.Item>
        ))}
      </Carousel>

      <Modal show={showModal} onHide={handleCloseModal} centered>
        <Modal.Body>
          <img src={selectedImage} alt="Expanded" className="img-fluid" />
        </Modal.Body>
      </Modal>
    </>
  );
}

export default ImageCarousel;
```

Here's how it works:

1. Import the `useState` hook from React and the `Modal` component from React Bootstrap.

2. Create two state variables using the `useState` hook:
   - `showModal`: Determines whether the modal is visible or not.
   - `selectedImage`: Stores the URL of the selected image to be displayed in the modal.

3. Create two event handler functions:
   - `handleImageClick`: Triggered when an image is clicked. It sets the `selectedImage` state to the clicked image URL and sets `showModal` to `true` to display the modal.
   - `handleCloseModal`: Triggered when the modal is closed. It sets `showModal` to `false` to hide the modal and clears the `selectedImage` state.

4. Modify the `<img>` element inside the `<Carousel.Item>` to include an `onClick` event handler that calls `handleImageClick` with the corresponding image URL.

5. Add a `<Modal>` component after the `<Carousel>` component. The `show` prop is set to the `showModal` state to control the visibility of the modal. The `onHide` prop is set to `handleCloseModal` to handle closing the modal.

6. Inside the `<Modal.Body>`, display the selected image using an `<img>` element with the `src` prop set to the `selectedImage` state.

With these modifications, when a user clicks on an image in the carousel, the `handleImageClick` function will be called, setting the `selectedImage` state to the clicked image URL and displaying the modal with the enlarged image. Clicking outside the modal or on the close button will trigger the `handleCloseModal` function, hiding the modal and clearing the `selectedImage` state.

Make sure you have the necessary CSS styles for the modal and the expanded image to achieve the desired visual appearance.

