To center and make the email card responsive, you can use a combination of flexbox, max-width, and margin auto:

```jsx
<div className="email-card-container">

  <Card 
    className="email-card"
    style={{maxWidth: '600px', backgroundColor: '#FFF'}}
  >
    {/* Card content */}
  </Card>

</div>
```

```css
.email-card-container {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
}

.email-card {
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 600px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .email-card {
    max-width: 90%;
  }
}
```

The key points:

- Use a wrapper div to center the card with flexbox
- Set max-width on the card itself 
- Margin auto for horizontal centering
- Media query to adjust max-width on smaller screens

This will keep the card centered and responsive.

Some other tips:

- You may want to set some vertical margin on the card
- Consider using CSS grid for alignment as well
- Use the Bootstrap .container class for a responsive width

