  height: 200px; /* Adjust the height as needed */
}

.carousel-item img {
  width: auto;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
}
```

Explanation:
- In the JSX code, within each `Carousel.Item`, a `div` with the classes `d-flex justify-content-center` is added to create a flex container for the images and center them horizontally.
- The `images.slice(i, i + 3)` is used to select a subset of three images starting from the current index `i`. This ensures that only three images are displayed side by side in each carousel item.
- The `img` elements are rendered with the class `d-inline-block mx-2` to display them inline and add horizontal margin between them.
- The `controls` prop of the `Carousel` component is set to `true` to display the previous and next controls for the slider.
- In the CSS code, the `carousel-item` class is given a fixed height (e.g., `200px`) to control the height of each carousel item. You can adjust this value as needed.
- The `carousel-item img` styles are updated to set the width to `auto` and height to `100%` to fit the images within the carousel item while maintaining their aspect ratio.

