for this banner image in my features section  i want to use the image from bannerref

To use the banner image from `bannerref` in your features section, you can modify the code as follows:

```jsx
const [imageUrls, setImageUrls] = useState([]);
const [bannerUrl, setBannerUrl] = useState('');

useEffect(() => {
    const fetchImageUrls = async () => {
        const storage = getStorage();
        const urls = [];
        try {
            for (let i = 1; i <= 4; i++) {
                const fileRef = ref(storage, `${i}card.jpg`);
                const url = await getDownloadURL(fileRef);
                urls.push(url);
            }
            setImageUrls(urls);
        } catch (error) {
            console.error('Error fetching image URLs:', error);
        }
    };

    const fetchBannerUrl = async () => {
        const storage = getStorage();
        const bannerRef = ref(storage, 'pineapplybanner.png');
        try {
            const url = await getDownloadURL(bannerRef);
            setBannerUrl(url);
        } catch (error) {
            console.error('Error fetching banner URL:', error);
        }
    };

    fetchImageUrls();
    fetchBannerUrl();
}, []);
```

Explanation:
1. We introduce a new state variable called `bannerUrl` using the `useState` hook to store the URL of the banner image.
2. Inside the `useEffect` hook, we create a new async function called `fetchBannerUrl` to fetch the banner image URL.
3. In the `fetchBannerUrl` function, we create a reference to the banner image using `ref(storage, 'pineapplybanner.png')`, assuming the banner image is stored in the root directory of your Firebase Storage with the name "pineapplybanner.png".
4. We use the `getDownloadURL` function to retrieve the download URL of the banner image.
5. Once we have the banner image URL, we update the `bannerUrl` state using the `setBannerUrl` function.
6. We call both `fetchImageUrls` and `fetchBannerUrl` functions inside the `useEffect` hook to fetch the image URLs and the banner URL when the component mounts.

Now, you can use the `bannerUrl` state variable to display the banner image in your features section. For example:

```jsx
<div className="features-section">
    <img src={bannerUrl} alt="Banner" className="banner-image" />
    {/* Other features content */}
</div>
```

Make sure to add appropriate styling for the `banner-image` class in your CSS file to position and size the banner image as desired.

With these modifications, the banner image will be fetched from Firebase Storage using the `bannerRef` and displayed in your features section.

