To make an element with the class `mb-4` a bit larger, you can increase its font size or add additional padding. Here's an example CSS code that increases the font size and adds padding:

```css
.mb-4 {
  font-size: 1.2rem;
  padding: 1rem;
}
```

In this CSS code:
- `font-size: 1.2rem;` increases the font size of the element to 1.2 times the root element's font size (typically 16px). You can adjust the value as needed.
- `padding: 1rem;` adds padding of 1 rem (which is equal to the root element's font size) on all sides of the element. This creates additional space around the content inside the element.

You can further customize the styles based on your specific requirements. For example, you can increase the padding on specific sides using `padding-top`, `padding-right`, `padding-bottom`, or `padding-left`, or you can add additional styles like background color, border, or margin to make the element visually larger.

Remember to adjust the values according to your design preferences and the overall layout of your webpage.

