WHY ISNT IT SHOWING M &quot;PROCESSING&quot; WHEN I CLICK SUBMIT

The reason why the button is not showing "Processing" when you click the submit button is likely because the `loading` state is not being updated correctly.

In the code snippet you provided, the button's text is conditionally rendered based on the value of the `loading` state. If `loading` is `true`, it should display "Processing...". Otherwise, it should display "Submit".

To ensure that the button shows "Processing" when clicked, you need to make sure that the `loading` state is being set to `true` when the submit button is clicked and before the processing starts.

Here's an example of how you can update the `handleSubmit` function to set the `loading` state:

```jsx
const handleSubmit = async () => {
  setLoading(true); // Set loading to true when the submit button is clicked

  try {
    // Your submission logic here
    // ...

    // Reset the loading state after the submission is complete
    setLoading(false);
  } catch (error) {
    // Handle any errors
    console.error('Error:', error);
    setLoading(false); // Reset the loading state in case of an error
  }
};
```

