The box is not centered in the middle of the page because the `container` div is not taking up the full height of the viewport. The `min-vh-100` class on the outer `div` ensures that the container takes up at least the full height of the viewport, but it doesn't center the content vertically.

To center the box vertically in the middle of the page, you can use flexbox utilities and adjust the CSS styles.

Here's the updated code:

```jsx
import React from 'react';
