              <div className="card-body">
                {/* ... */}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <Footer />
    </div>
  );
};

export default PrivacyPolicy;
```

And here's the updated CSS:

```css
.privacy-policy-heading {
  color: purple;
}

@media (max-width: 767px) {
  .card {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
}
```

In the updated code:

1. The `container` div now has the classes `d-flex flex-column justify-content-center align-items-center flex-grow-1`. This ensures that the container takes up the remaining vertical space (`flex-grow-1`), and its contents are vertically centered (`justify-content-center`) and horizontally centered (`align-items-center`).
2. The `my-auto` class has been removed from the `container` div since it's no longer needed.

With these changes, the box containing the privacy policy content should now be centered vertically and horizontally in the middle of the page.

