The reason why `imageUrls` is still printing as an empty array is because the `fetchImageUrls` function is asynchronous, and the `console.log('Image URLs:', imageUrls);` statement is executed before the asynchronous operation completes and populates the `imageUrls` array.

To fix this issue, you can move the `console.log` statement inside the `fetchImageUrls` function, specifically after the `imageUrls.push(...urls);` line. This way, the `imageUrls` array will be logged after it has been populated with the fetched image URLs.

Here's the updated code:

```javascript
let imageUrls = [];

import { getStorage, ref, listAll, getDownloadURL } from 'firebase/storage';
import { storage } from '../../firebaseauth.js';

const dreamlookApiKey = 'dl-F3BFCB0668D04BE4BE9E5C1DDC2AB0A4';
const baseUrl = 'http://training-cheri.s3-website-us-east-1.amazonaws.com/vadim/';

const fetchImageUrls = async () => {
    const folderRef = ref(storage, 'kareemy9000_gmail_com/');

    try {
        const listResult = await listAll(folderRef);
        const urlPromises = listResult.items.map((itemRef) => getDownloadURL(itemRef));
        const urls = await Promise.all(urlPromises);
        imageUrls.push(...urls);
        console.log('Image URLs:', imageUrls); // Log the imageUrls array here
    } catch (error) {
        console.error('Error fetching KAREEMY9000 AI image URLs:', error);
    }
};

fetchImageUrls();
```

Now, when you run this code, the `console.log('Image URLs:', imageUrls);` statement will be executed after the `imageUrls` array has been populated with the image URLs fetched from Firebase Storage.

Alternatively, if you want to access the `imageUrls` array outside the `fetchImageUrls` function, you can return the `imageUrls` array from the function and handle it using a `.then` callback or an `async/await` approach.

Here's an example using the `.then` callback:

```javascript
let imageUrls = [];

import { getStorage, ref, listAll, getDownloadURL } from 'firebase/storage';
import { storage } from '../../firebaseauth.js';

const dreamlookApiKey = 'dl-F3BFCB0668D04BE4BE9E5C1DDC2AB0A4';
const baseUrl = 'http://training-cheri.s3-website-us-east-1.amazonaws.com/vadim/';

const fetchImageUrls = async () => {
    const folderRef = ref(storage, 'kareemy9000_gmail_com/');

    try {
        const listResult = await listAll(folderRef);
        const urlPromises = listResult.items.map((itemRef) => getDownloadURL(itemRef));
        const urls = await Promise.all(urlPromises);
        imageUrls.push(...urls);
        return imageUrls;
    } catch (error) {
        console.error('Error fetching KAREEMY9000 AI image URLs:', error);
    }
};

fetchImageUrls()
    .then((urls) => {
        console.log('Image URLs:', urls);
        // You can access the imageUrls array here
    })
    .catch((error) => {
        console.error('Error:', error);
    });
```

