To show the `<HeadshotSuccess />` component only when the form submission is successful, you can use a conditional rendering technique in React. Here's how you can modify your code:

1. First, add a state variable to keep track of the form submission status. You can initialize it to `false` and update it to `true` when the form submission is successful.

```jsx
const [isSubmitSuccessful, setIsSubmitSuccessful] = useState(false);
```

2. In your `handleSubmit` function, where you handle the form submission logic, update the `isSubmitSuccessful` state to `true` after a successful submission.

```jsx
const handleSubmit = async (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    // Your form submission logic...

    // If the submission is successful
    setIsSubmitSuccessful(true);
};
```

3. In your JSX, use a conditional rendering technique to show the `<HeadshotSuccess />` component only when `isSubmitSuccessful` is `true`.

```jsx
return (
    <>
        {/* Your form elements */}

        {isSubmitSuccessful && (
            <div className="headshot-success">
                <HeadshotSuccess />
            </div>
        )}
    </>
);
```

With these changes, the `<HeadshotSuccess />` component will only be rendered when the `isSubmitSuccessful` state is `true`, which happens after a successful form submission.

Here's the complete code with the changes:

```jsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import HeadshotSuccess from './headshotsuccess.jsx';

const Headshot = () => {
    const [isSubmitSuccessful, setIsSubmitSuccessful] = useState(false);

    const handleSubmit = async (e) => {
        e.preventDefault();
        // Your form submission logic...

        // If the submission is successful
        setIsSubmitSuccessful(true);
    };

    return (
        <>
            {/* Your form elements */}
            <form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
                {/* Form inputs */}
                <button type="submit">Submit</button>
            </form>

            {isSubmitSuccessful && (
                <div className="headshot-success">
                    <HeadshotSuccess />
                </div>
            )}
        </>
    );
};

export default Headshot;
```

In this example, the `<HeadshotSuccess />` component will be rendered inside the `<div className="headshot-success">` only when `isSubmitSuccessful` is `true`, which happens after a successful form submission.

To show the `<HeadshotSuccess />` component in place of the `<Card>` component after a successful form submission, you can modify your code as follows:

```jsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import HeadshotSuccess from './headshotsuccess.jsx';
import Card from 'react-bootstrap/Card';

const Headshot = () => {
    const [isSubmitSuccessful, setIsSubmitSuccessful] = useState(false);

    const handleSubmit = async (e) => {
        e.preventDefault();
        // Your form submission logic...

        // If the submission is successful
        setIsSubmitSuccessful(true);
    };

    return (
        <>
            {/* Your form elements */}
            <form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
                {/* Form inputs */}
                <button type="submit">Submit</button>
            </form>

            {!isSubmitSuccessful && (
                <Card className="upload-card my-4" style={{ width: '100%', maxWidth: '800px', borderRadius: '25px' }}>
                    {/* Card content */}
                </Card>
            )}

            {isSubmitSuccessful && (
                <div className="headshot-success">
                    <HeadshotSuccess />
                </div>
            )}
        </>
    );
};

export default Headshot;
```

In this updated code:

1. We render the `<Card>` component only when `isSubmitSuccessful` is `false` using the condition `{!isSubmitSuccessful && (...)}`.
2. We render the `<HeadshotSuccess />` component only when `isSubmitSuccessful` is `true` using the condition `{isSubmitSuccessful && (...)}`.

With this approach, the `<Card>` component will be displayed initially, and after a successful form submission (when `isSubmitSuccessful` becomes `true`), the `<HeadshotSuccess />` component will replace the `<Card>` component.

Make sure to import the `Card` component from the appropriate library (e.g., `react-bootstrap` in this case) and adjust the styles and content of the `<Card>` component as needed.

