To use MUI Joy instead of MUI Material, you need to import the components from the `@mui/joy` package instead of `@mui/material`. Here's the updated code with MUI Joy components:

```jsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar/Navbar.jsx';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer/Footer.jsx';
import axios from 'axios';
import { Container, Typography, Input, Button, Grid, Sheet } from '@mui/joy';

const Laborbotpage = () => {
    const [userInput, setUserInput] = useState('');
    const [chatbotResponse, setChatbotResponse] = useState('');

    const handleChatbotRequest = async () => {
        try {
            const response = await axios.post(
                'https://hope-56ogefmcva-ww.a.run.app/',
                {
                    user_question: userInput,
                }
            );
            setChatbotResponse(response.data.answer);
        } catch (error) {
            console.error('Error communicating with chatbot:', error);
            setChatbotResponse(
                'Apologies, an error occurred. Please try again later.'
            );
        }
    };

    return (
        <>
            <Navbar />
            <Container maxWidth="md" sx={{ my: 4 }}>
                <Sheet variant="outlined" sx={{ p: 4 }}>
                    <Typography level="h4" textAlign="center" mb={2}>
                        Labor Law Chatbot
                    </Typography>
                    <Grid container spacing={2}>
                        <Grid item xs={12}>
                            <Input
                                placeholder="Ask a question"
                                fullWidth
                                value={userInput}
                                onChange={(e) => setUserInput(e.target.value)}
                            />
                        </Grid>
                        <Grid item xs={12}>
                            <Button
                                variant="solid"
                                color="primary"
                                fullWidth
                                onClick={handleChatbotRequest}
                            >
                                Submit
                            </Button>
                        </Grid>
                        <Grid item xs={12}>
                            <Sheet
                                sx={{
                                    bgcolor: 'background.body',
                                    p: 2,
                                    minHeight: 200,
                                    overflowY: 'auto',
                                }}
                            >
                                {chatbotResponse && (
                                    <Typography level="body1">
                                        {chatbotResponse}
                                    </Typography>
                                )}
                            </Sheet>
                        </Grid>
                    </Grid>
                </Sheet>
            </Container>
            <Footer />
        </>
    );
};

export default Laborbotpage;
```

Here are the changes made:

1. Imported components from `@mui/joy` instead of `@mui/material`.
2. Replaced `Paper` with `Sheet` from MUI Joy.
3. Replaced `TextField` with `Input` from MUI Joy.
4. Replaced `variant` and `color` prop values with MUI Joy equivalents.
5. Replaced `gutterBottom` with `mb={2}` for bottom margin.
6. Replaced `align` with `textAlign` for text alignment.

Note that MUI Joy has a different styling approach and component naming conventions compared to MUI Material. You may need to adjust other styles and props accordingly based on the MUI Joy documentation.

