```

Here are the changes made:

1. Wrapped the entire component with a `div` element.
2. Set the `display` property of the `div` to `flex` and `flexDirection` to `column`.
3. Set the `minHeight` of the `div` to `100vh` (100% of the viewport height).
4. Added `flexGrow: 1` to the `Container` component to make it take up the remaining vertical space.

By using flexbox, we create a flex container with a column layout. The `minHeight: 100vh` ensures that the flex container takes up the full height of the viewport. The `flexGrow: 1` on the `Container` component allows it to grow and take up the remaining vertical space, pushing the `Footer` component to the bottom.

This approach should make the footer stick to the bottom of the page, regardless of the content height.

